can you pick up a ball python while it's in a ball well if your snake is in a ball its obviously because it is feeling a little scared if the snake does this every time you pick it up you may need to handle it more at the same time dont handle it every day because if the snake is timid you dont want to stress it out to much so handle the snake every other day for lets say ten minutes at a time eventually you can start to lengthen the time you handle it at a time this should help with the shyness so to answer your question yes you can handle your snake when its in a ball because you want to tame it a little more but not too often as it will cause stress also which could throw the bp off frozen thawed rodents but just keep a good balance and all will be fine Snake charming Shaggy dog story Singlish Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Indian cricket team in Zimbabwe in 2005-06 Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 Laws of cricket Norway national football team Creatures in Bionicle Croquet Cricket National Football League Lore Snake New York Giants Toilet humour Carbon dioxide Piccolo Junior Saga Skeletor Escape from New York Dodgeball Burmese python Aurelian Smith, Jr. The Contender (television series) Slayer (Buffy the Vampire Slayer) Knife Cleveland Browns Happy Tree Friends Water polo Son Goku (Dragon Ball) Sydney Riot of 1879 Tag Pittsburgh Steelers Aerial (dance move) Cincinnati Bengals The Amazing Maurice and his Educated Rodents Equine conformation Church of God with Signs Following Exception handling Ron and Fez Brian Close Volleyball Solid Snake The Life and Times of Juniper Lee American football Sly Cooper Ball python Sword making Videocon Tri-Series 2005-06 Wood carving Atomic Kitten Football (soccer) Shen Gong Wu Serpent Society Jennifer Lopez The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time characters Alignment (role-playing games) Cat Alex Trebek 1957 World Series Metal Gear Solid: The Twin Snakes The Adventures of Pete & Pete Avalanche Touch footba